node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY on September 17, 2021 tagging @mementopdx. May be an image of cloud and text.

node.text:
Happy Friday and Challenge Announcement Day, JJMP fam!! 🥳🎉🙋🏻‍♀️ 
.
I’m on Cloud 9 that David @mementopdx is hosting his first JJMP weekend challenge for us!! 😃💙⛅️ 
Please give him a warm welcome and 
Then, read below for more insight into his creative mindset and imagination-inspiring theme.😃 💫 
.
.
.
“Hello mobile family! My name is David (@mementopdx), and I am thrilled that Dee (@iheart_alfresco_photos) and Jax (@jaxkm2) have asked me to be a guest moderator for this weekend’s challenge. I have been a photography enthusiast most of my life, but it is only recently that I discovered online communities that share that enthusiasm and genuinely encourage one another like @jj_mobilephotography and @raw_mobile_
.

Mobile photography reminds me of the catch phrase in the Pixar film, “Ratatouille”, “Anyone can cook” meaning that not everyone can be a great artist, but great art can come from anyone, from anywhere, and be about anything. My mobile camera is never far away, and I find that looking at the world through my always-at-the-ready camera lens changes how I see it. Details that I would have otherwise overlooked, often become the center point of an unfolding story.

I’m calling this weekend’s challenge theme “Look Again”. At first glance the meaning of a photograph may be obvious, but if you look at it again through the lens of your imagination you see something completely different. At first glance, the photo above is of a cloud break at dusk. But if you “look again” you might see warring Genie masters  rub their lamps as they prepare for battle, or maybe if you “look again” you can see steam trains of unsuspecting lovers just pass one another into the night.

Tell me what you see in your post. Use your imagination and have fun with it.” ~ David (@mementopdx) 
.
.
Theme: “Look Again” 
.
.
‼️Challenge Rules:‼️
▶️ MUST be following @jj_mobilephotography
▶️ Specify which mobile device you’re using.
.
.
Tag #jj_mobilephoto_325 👈
.
.
▶️New or old photos okay
.
▶️No previously featured (here on @jj_mobilephotography) photos please
.
#jj_mp_mementopdx 
Please pay our featured artist’s gallery a visit and show it some jjmp L❤️VE. Thanks!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Romania with @johnnlyme. May be a black-and-white image of drink and indoor.

node.text:
Hello, JJMP Fam! 😘💖🙋🏻‍♀️

What an enlightening weekend challenge and day its been at JJMP today!!🤩🖤

Please take a moment to congratulate our 5 fabulous photographers featured today and also our  guest mod, Michelle, @michzsimmons for her superb job of hosting for us. 
And we thank y’all as always for tagging, participating and following along with JJMP each week.💞🤗 
.
.
Finally the moment we’ve all been waiting for has arrived: the BIG reveal of Michelle’s first place winner from this weekend’s challenge!! 🏅 

So grab a seat and a cup of your favorite  beverage and let’s read all about what made this picture really shine above the rest for our guest mod this weekend and hear her thoughts on this challenge. ⭐️ 🥳 🎊 🏆 
.
.
.
.
.
@johnnlyme 
.
.
.
.
“For me, this photo perfectly demonstrates how a backlit photo is both a skill and an art. The directional lighting creates a beautiful glow around the edges of the subject, highlighting even the tiny hairs of the “reader’s” head and face. The photographer’s perfect exposure puts the figure in silhouette while maintaining great detail in the secondary subjects. This kept my eye moving around the image for a long time! Excellent work, Ionut. Congratulations. 

As we end with the “backlighting” challenge, I’d like to sincerely thank everyone that participated. I was so impressed with every single entry. You know how sometimes you see a photo and think “wow, I wish I had taken that?” Well I can’t believe how many times that happened in this challenge! Congrats to all of you for your beautiful entries, and thank you to Dee and Jax for allowing me to be a part of this process. It was truly an honor.” ~ Michelle @michzsimmons 
.
.
.
.
.
Featured artist: @johnnlyme 
#jj_mp_johnnlyme 
.
.
.
Please pay our featured artist’s gallery a visit and show it some jjmp L❤️VE. Thanks!

node.text:
Well, JJMP Fam, Here we are at the last of Guest Mod Michelle’s @michzsimmons “runner ups”  from her “Backlighting” weekend challenge before unveiling her TOP winner in a few hours!! (😵Can you stand the anticipation?!?😜) 

So now is the PuRRR…fect time to “paws” for dramatic effect…..😸😽🖤🤍

and find out what she loves about her final of 4 “runner ups” in no particular order. 😻
.
.
.
.
.
@fatherofdogs 
.
.
.
“This photo attracts me because of its composition, contrast and perfect exposure. The color of the cats, along with the photographer’s skill, put one cat in silhouette while the other is full of detail.  I also love how the dark cat is silhouetted, but you can still see a highlight in his eye and detailed fur on the tip of his tail. Great work, Dean.” ~ Michelle @michzsimmons 
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
JJMP Fam, It’s time to shine another spotlight on Guest Mod Michelle’s @michzsimmons next fave from her “Backlighting” weekend challenge!! 🌞💙🌟 

It’s pretty clear what made this natural beauty stand out and shine for Michelle but let’s hear what she loves most about her 3rd of 4 “runner ups” in no particular order.😍
.
.
.
.
.
@nature.lookout 
.
.
.
“I love this photo for its overall beauty, but I especially like how the photographer made the subject glow. When the sun is directly behind a subject, it usually results in a stark silhouette, but this photo is exposed to create a “halo” around the flower. This technique reveals just enough detail to keep your eye lingering there. I couldn’t stop looking at it. Great photography, Clara.” ~ Michelle @michzsimmons 
.
.
.
.
.
.
Featured artist: @nature.lookout
